&lt;p&gt;Barnet, Enfield and Haringey Mental Health Trust are looking to recruit Trust Doctors (ST4+ equivalent) in the following Psychiatry posts to start as soon as possible until 3rd August 2021.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Please refer to the job description for more information for each post.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Post 1 - General Adult Psychiatry, Barnet, Full Time&lt;br /&gt;Post 2 - Liaison Psychiatry, Barnet, Full Time&lt;br /&gt;Post 3 - Old Age Psychiatry, Barnet, Full Time&lt;br /&gt;Post 4 - General Adult Psychiatry, Enfield, Full Time&lt;br /&gt;Post 7 - Intellectual Disability, Haringey, Full Time&lt;br /&gt;Post 8 - Eating Disorders, Specialist Services, Full Time&lt;br /&gt;Post 10 - General Adult Psychiatry, Barnet, Full Time&lt;br /&gt;Post 13 - General Adult Psychiatry, Barnet, Full Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post 14 - General Adult/ Old Age Psyciatry, Haringey, Part Time (36 Hours)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whilst these are not training posts we are providing you with the opportunity to develop your skills and competencies in psychiatry with the aim to assisting you in gaining the necessary experience to apply for training posts within the region. The duties of the post, performance criteria and the learning opportunities are matched against the learning outcomes based on the curriculum competencies for Psychiatry specialities.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In the event of further opportunities becoming available shortlisted candidates may also be considered for these posts.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please state which post(s) you are applying for within your application in the supporting statement section.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*Note that the vacancies advertised may be subject to change prior to interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;*Strictly no agencies please&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;br /&gt;Please refer to the Job description&lt;/p&gt;
